I'll create a comprehensive game hub website script with an easy way to manage games. This will include a frontend interface and a simple backend system.I can help you create a game hub website! The tool provided a good foundation, but let me create a more complete and feature-rich version for you. 

Here's a comprehensive game hub script with an easy game management system:

## Frontend - HTML (index.html)

```html name=index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Game Hub - Play Now!</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="header-content">
            <h1>🎮 Game Hub</h1>
            <button id="add-game-btn" class="admin-btn">+ Add Game</button>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main>
        <div id="game-grid" class="game-grid"></div>
    </main>

    <!-- Modal for adding games -->
    <div id="game-modal" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close">&times;</span>
            <h2>Add New Game</h2>
            <form id="game-form">
                <input type="text" id="game-title" placeholder="Game Title" required>
                <input type="url" id="game-url" placeholder="Game URL (iframe embed link)" required>
                <textarea id="game-description" placeholder="Game Description"></textarea>
                <input type="text" id="game-image" placeholder="Image URL (thumbnail)">
                <button type="submit">Add Game</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Game Player Modal -->
    <div id="player-modal" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content player-modal-content">
            <span class="close">&times;</span>
            <h2 id="player-title"></h2>
            <iframe id="game-frame" src="" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Frontend - CSS (styles.css)

```css name=styles.css
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
